Unlimited Sale of Valuable Young Negroes. 
             BY JA BEARD & RICHARDSON. 

Will be sold at auction on Tuesday, 16 inst, at 12 o'clock, at Banks' Arcade, the following described negroes, all of whom are from one owner and can be well recommended, and are sold for no fault, viz: 
Jim. a likely Boy aged 12 years house boy.
HARRIET, likely Negress, 13 years, child's n[u]rse and house girl. 
ELLEN,       "           15              "       do      do 
AMERICA   "           15              "           field hand, &c. 
TABITHA    "            16             "           good house girl, 
washer, ironer and sews well. 
ETTY, aged 15 years, nurse and house girl. 
ANN, aged 20 years, field hand and house women and her child aged 1 year. 
JONAS aged 22 years, field hand. 
DANIEL, aged 25 years, field hand, and a good rope maker and spinner. 
RYLAND, aged 26 years, field hand, and good waggoner and drayman. 
CYRUS, aged 23 years, mulatto, good cook, waiter, coachman and first rate barber. 
The above Negroes are very likely, and fully guarantied against the vices and maladies prescribed by law. 
Terms- cash. 
Acts of sale before J B Marks, Notary Publie, at the expense of the purchaser. 
The slaves can be treated for at private sale previous to Tuesday               m15
